fr.inria.atlanmod.mogwai.mapping

Class AbstractMapping

  • Object
    • AbstractMapping
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    EMFtoGraphMapping
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    NeoEMFMapping

    public abstract class AbstractMapping
extends Object
implements EMFtoGraphMapping
    An implementation of EMFtoGraphMapping that defines all Pipeline and Pipe related methods as wrapper of existing methods.

    This class can be extended by concrete mappings to provide the logic of the mapping, avoiding the definition of Gremlin related concepts such as Pipes. Note that it is still possible to redifine Pipe related methods to provide additional behavior within a traversal.

    Author:
    Gwendal DANIEL
    See Also:
    EMFtoGraphMapping

      • isTypeOf

        public Pipe<Vertex,Boolean> isTypeOf(String type)
        Returns a Pipe that computes for each input element whether it is an instance of type.

        Note: the created Pipe only checks if its input elements are strict instances of type. To check if they are instances of type or any of its subclasses see EMFtoGraphMapping.isKindOf(Vertex, String) and EMFtoGraphMapping.isKindOf(String).

        The created Pipe uses isTypeOf(Vertex, String) to compute whether its input elements are instances of type.

        Specified by:
